Mr. Chamberlain, who is also a professor at Quisqueya University, said of the UWCI: “These project convinced me to work with the Project because Haitian entrepreneurs are smart people; they need a helping when they want to start a business. It would make a big difference if a contestant got funding from a bank or a business partner, but it is just like a wish come true. So the best thing we can do is give them the opportunity in Education and Health. So I hope this Project will make a big difference in our community.”
